{{Infobox person | name = Kitty Anderson | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Icelandic | residence = | education = | occupation = Community activist | known_for = Intersex activist, co-chair of [[OII Europe]] | website = }}
'''Kitty Anderson''' is an [[intersex]] activist from Iceland. She is a co-chair of European intersex organization [[OII Europe]], a co-founder of Intersex Iceland, and chairman of the board of the [[Icelandic Human Rights Centre]].<ref name="ihrc">{{Cite web|url = http://www.humanrights.is/en/about-us/board-and-partners | title = Board and Partners | website = [[Icelandic Human Rights Centre]] | accessdate = 2018-11-23}}</ref> She has been described as a "leading voice of the intersex movement in Europe."<ref name="ilga" />
== Background ==
Kitty Anderson was born with [[androgen insensitivity syndrome|androgen insensitivity]]. She found out when she was 13, but only found out she was born with internal testes when she was aged 22.<ref name="interface">{{Cite web |url=https://www.interfaceproject.org/kitty-anderson/ |title=Kitty Anderson – Reykjavík, Iceland |website=[[Interact Advocates for Intersex Youth#Interface Project|Interface Project]] |date=October 2017| accessdate = 2018-11-22}}</ref><ref name="amnesty">{{Cite web |author=Amnesty International |title=Understanding the 'i' in LGBTI |accessdate=2018-11-22 |date=October 25, 2016 |url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2016/10/intersex-awareness-day/}}</ref> Anderson has reported that her "mother was told to lie" to her until she was aged 13.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://grapevine.is/news/2018/02/19/iceland-violates-human-rights-by-performing-surgery-on-intersex-children/ |title=Iceland Violates Human Rights By Performing Surgery On Intersex Children |first=Alice |last=Demurtas |website=The Reykjavik Grapevine |date=February 19, 2018 |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.visir.is/g/2015705239975 |title=Við vorum einar í heiminum |first=Kristjana |last=Björg Guðbrandsdóttir |website=Visir |date=May 23, 2015 |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref>
== Activism ==
Anderson co-founded Intersex Iceland in 2014,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://interactadvocates.org/aic-guest-blog-kitty-anderson-intersex-iceland/ |title=AIC Guest Blog Kitty Anderson, Intersex Iceland |website=[[Interact Advocates for Intersex Youth]] |date=October 27, 2014 |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref> and currently serves as its chairperson.<ref name="interface" /> She is co-chair and spokesperson<ref name="me">{{cite web |url=http://cherna.gora.me/government/idaho-2015-montenegros-government-contributes-significantly-to-holding-of-14th-roundtable-of-european-governmental-lgbt-focal-points-network/ |title=IDAHO 2015: Montenegro’s government contributes significantly to holding of 14th Roundtable of European Governmental LGBT Focal Points Network |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=May 12, 2015 |website= |publisher=Government of [[Montenegro]] |access-date=2015-07-02 |quote=}}</ref> of [[OII Europe]] and chairperson of the board of the [[Icelandic Human Rights Centre]].<ref name="ihrc"/> She has also served on the board of [[Samtökin '78]], Iceland's national queer organization, and the national Ministry of Welfare Queer Committee from 2014-2016.<ref name="interface" /> Anderson has spoken against secrecy and shame associated with intersex:
{{quotation|When I found out I was 13 and I completely freaked out. There can be a lot of secrecy and stigma related to being intersex and it was something that had been kept from me. But when my cousin – who is also intersex – was born a couple of years later, my family didn’t keep it a secret and it was a healing process for all of us <ref name="amnesty" />}}
She also campaigns against [[intersex medical interventions]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://oiieurope.org/video-frontline-dispatches-intersex-children-and-medical-sex-assignment-whose-right-to-choose/ |title=[VIDEO] Frontline Dispatches: Intersex Children And Medical Sex Assignment – Whose Right To Choose? |website=[[OII Europe]] |date=June 10, 2016 |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://hinsegindagar.is/en/puppets-controlled-by-the-system/ |title=Puppets controlled by the system |website=Reykjavik Pride |date=July 16, 2015 |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref> In an interview with NIKK, Anderson has stated that "surgeries will continue until we get a law that prohibits them".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nikk.no/en/news/bodies-obviously-undesirable/ |title=Some bodies are obviously undesirable |website=NIKK |date=October 4, 2016 |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref>
Anderson has presented to the [[Council of Europe]] Committee on Bioethics,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.coe.int/en/web/sogi/-/bioethics-committee-discusses-the-human-rights-of-intersex-and-transgender-children-and-young-people?desktop=true |title=Bioethics committee discussed the human rights of intersex and transgender children and young people |website=[[Council of Europe]] |date=June 1, 2016 |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref> and speaks at a range of conferences,<ref name="ilga">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ilga-europe.org/conference/nicosia-2016/speakers |title=Speakers – Nicosia 2016 |website=[[ILGA-Europe]] |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.intersex-conference.at/english/Programme/ |title=Intersex Conference Vienna 2017 |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref> media,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mbl.is/frettir/innlent/2018/02/16/tharf_ad_tryggja_mannrettindi_intersex_folks/ |title=Þarf að tryggja mannréttindi intersex fólks |website=mbl.is |date=February 16, 2018 |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite |title=Intersex Education |work=[[Gay Community News (Dublin)|GCN]] |first=Chris |last=O'Donnell |pages=100–103 |date=June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://cyprus-mail.com/2016/11/11/a-different-biology/ |title=A different biology |website=[[Cyprus Mail]] |date=November 11, 2016 |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref> and human rights institutions across Scandinavia and Europe.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/portugal-lgbt-lawmaking/portugal-approves-law-to-boost-transgender-rights-protect-intersex-infants-idUSL1N1RQ0ZP |title=Portugal approves law to boost transgender rights, protect intersex infants |website=Reuters |first=Kieran |last=Guilbert |date=April 14, 2018 |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref>
In 2015, Anderson campaigned to change terminology in the biology curriculum in Icelandic schools, and dictionaries, after finding out that the word intersex was being translated into Icelandic as "freak".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://gayiceland.is/2015/not-teaching-prejudice/ |title=We Should Not Be Teaching Prejudice in Our Schools |first=Halla |last=Þórlaug Óskarsdóttir |website=Gay Iceland |date=August 10, 2015 |accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://oiiuk.org/1463/we-should-not-be-teaching-prejudice/ |title=We Should Not Be Teaching Prejudice |first=Leslie |last=J |website=[[Organisation Intersex International|OII-UK]] |date=October 8, 2015 | accessdate=2018-11-23}}</ref> The publisher of the school text later apologized.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://gayiceland.is/2015/publisher-apologises-poor-translation/ |title=Publisher Apologizes for Poor Translation |first=Roald |last=Eyvindsson |website=Gay Iceland |date=August 10, 2015}}</ref>
